sourceQuestion:
The head of a hard disk serves requests following the shortest seek time first (SSTF) policy. The head is initially positioned at track number 100. Which of the following request sets will cause the head to change its direction after servicing every request, assuming that the head does not change direction if there is a request at the same distance in both directions?
A. {11, 130, 170, 171, 144, 301, 305}
B. {10, 130, 170, 175, 151, 201, 205}
C. {10, 150, 130, 123, 151, 205, 302}
D. {10, 130, 175, 150, 201, 151, 205}

Consider the following code fragment:

int a = 10;
if (fork() == 0) {
    a = a + 5;
    printf("%d, %p\n", a, &a);
} else {
    a = a - 5;
    printf("%d, %p\n", a, &a);
}

Let x be the values printed by the parent process and y be the values printed by the child process. Which one of the following is TRUE?

A. x = 10 and y = 15
B. x = 10 and y = 15 and the virtual address of a in the parent and child are the same
C. x = 5 and y = 15 and the virtual address of a in the parent and child are different
D. x = 5 and y = 15 and the virtual address of a in the parent and child are the same

